Business Brief -- Rohm  Haas Co.:
   Firm to Buy 70% of Shipley
   It Doesn't Already Have
Since 1982, Rohm  Haas has owned 30% of the common stock
of the Newton, Mass., maker of electronic chemicals.
Shipley's world-wide sales of about $200 million include
photoresist and specialty chemical products for the
semiconductor and printed circuit board industries.
   Rohm  Haas, a chemical concern, said it expects to
complete the acquisition in the second quarter.
   The company said that Richard Shipley will remain
president and become chief executive officer of the unit.